name: Antique Richard Dey Ribcowsky ships at sunset framed lithograph print
description:
Antique Richard Dey Ribcowsky ships at sunset framed lithograph print

I love this beautiful big bright picture. It is a large ships or schooners at sunset print by American/Bulgarian artist Richard Dey Ribcowsky (1880-1936). Original painted around 1920s. Print from 1930s set in a large heavy ornate wood frame painted gold.

Print is in excellent condition - there are a couple of tiny patches where the print has rubbed off - in the far top right hand corner and on the side at the lower left. 

The heavy ornate wood frame has a couple of small chips in the paint.

Frame is 33" (84cm) wide X 27"(69cm) high X 2 1/2" (7cm) deep.

Pick up available in Sydney. if you live outside Australia please contact me for shipping quote.

name: Vintage statement boho tribal necklace of metal and glass beads
description:
Vintage statement boho tribal necklace of metal and glass beads

This is a serious look at me necklace - the sort of tribal bling so popular in the early nineties and experiencing a real comeback now. The colours are pure Africa - orange, greens and reds. A confection of different size and shape glass and metal beads - multi strand around the neck and then a cascade with tassels ending in copper discs. 

It is a very classy piece of jewelery, beautifully finished with lobster clasp and safety chain in brass.

It is in excellent vintage condition - the hanging centrepiece is 10 1/2" (27cm) long X 2" (5cm) wide.

This is a very special piece of costume jewelry and quite comfortably light to wear and beautifully made. It has a delightful soft jangly noise that shell makes - very boho!

name: Vintage mid century designer Lederer of Paris lizard skin gold plated box handbag
description:
Vintage mid century designer Lederer of Paris lizard skin box handbag


Beautiful rare designer bag made by Lederer of Paris circa 1940s/1950s. 

I love the styling and the solidity of this bag - beautiful fine lizard skin - shiny and black in contrast to the thick strips of gold plated metal that edge the bag. Every inch of this is designer class.

Lederer is a fashion house still producing excellent quality hand bags in Paris. Inside it is printed in gold with " Made in France Especially for Lederer"

In very good to excellent vintage condition. Some wear in the lizard skin on the edges and corner of the bag and on the handles and some scratches and wear on the gold, particularly the clasp at the top. The handles are solidly attached but there are a couple of cracks in the external lizard skin near the base of each handle. Does not effect its performance. Clasp is still very firm.

Inside it is pristine - lined in smooth black leather - it has one main compartment with a buttoned down twin pocket on one side (fits a mobile!) and two open pockets on the other.

It is 8 3/4" (22cm) wide X 5 1/2" (14cm) high X 3 1/4" (8.5cm) deep. 

A beautiful and unusual vintage bag for a special occasion.

name: Modernist atomic metal tube cylinder ikebana vase
description:
Modernist atomic silver tone metal tube ikebana vase

This is a striking collection of metal tubes welded together to form a very interesting ikebana flower vase. From the 1960s it is heavy set to hold the heaviest flower you can throw at it.

In excellent vintage condition - silver and gold tone.
&" (18cm) high X 2" (5cm) at the base.

name: Vintage retro 1960s orange and tan plaid mohair wool picnic travel blanket throw
description:
Vintage retro 1960s orange and tan plaid mohair wool picnic travel blanket throw

Love these picnic blankets - my parents always kept one in the car for those impromptu picnics!
Gorgeously soft and snuggly in bright oranges and tan plaid with fringed edge.

In excellent vintage condition -

Made by St Albans in Australia from 100% pure scottish mohair.

It is 67" (170cm) X 50" (125cm).

name: Mid century modern art print Young Girl in Repose by Tugomir Huburger
description:
Mid century modern art print Young Girl in Repose by German artist Tugomir Huburger

Fabulous pure 1963 art print of a reclining nude by Tugomir Huburger (1931-2001).
Very stylish and in keeping with the aesthetics of the time. I love the bright colours and linework.
Large art print by Kunst im Druk in 1963. 

25" (64cm) wide X 37 1/2" (95cm) long.

In very good vintage condition - this is a quality art print on heavy rag based paper. There is a short tear on the white background and the paper is a bit yellow and has a few grubby spots from age. There are a couple of patches of torn patches of paper on the corners at the back where it has been hung. But the actual print is spectacular in colour and clarity.

A beautiful addition to a retro home.

name: Mid century Glomesh beige enamel mesh handbag
description:
Beautiful 1960s Glomesh cream/beige enamel metal mesh handbag with a very nice golden swirl marble effect resin top and thick chain handle. Nice solid base - sits firmly p the table.

In very good vintage condition - two small squares of mesh are missing - one on the bottom and one on the back.

It is 12" (31cm) wide X 7' (18cm) highX 3" (7cm) deep.

name: Mid Century pair green glazed Chinese porcelain foo dog candle holders
description:
Mid century Chinoiserie lucky foo dogs for your table.

Originating in the Han dynasty in China - the imperial guardian lion (known as foo dogs in the west). They were believed to have powerful mythic protective benefits and statues of guardian lions have traditionally stood in front of important buildings. They always come in pairs.

This mid century ceramic pair have green glazed surface and hold up to a 1" (2cm) diameter dinner candle in each. 

In excellent vintage condition - 3 3/4" (10cm) wide X 3" (7cm) deep X 8" (21cm) high.
